SIMPLE: uniparous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uniparous
<hw>U*nip"a*rous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Uni-</ets>
+ L. <ets>parere</ets> to bring forth.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Producing but one egg or young at a
time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Producing but one axis of
inflorescence; -- said of the scorpioid cyme.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uniped</ent>⟦br⟧
